    "Commentary Vol. 90": "The name Bethany `[place_Bethany_Ref]` appears to mean either 'house of dates' or 'house of the poor.' There was another Bethany `[place_Bethany_Ref]` beyond Jordan, (John `[char_John_Ref]` 1:28) and in John `[char_John_Ref]` 11:1 this Bethany `[place_Bethany_Ref]` is distinguished as \"the vil age of Mary `[char_Mary_Ref]` and her sister Martha.\" [v_Mat_21_12] Microsoft Word - John `[char_John_Ref]` Broadus' Commentary on Matthew Homiletical And Practical Matthew 21:\n18. As he returned , or probably, upon returning (1) He hungered . The first meal was usually taken about the middle of the forenoon. (Acts 2:15) Compare on Matthew 22:",
